@node Main "Building - Documentation"

                              Building 1.06

                       Created by Charles-N. Jacob

  A major electrical overload happened in a high-rise @{"building" link play}
(well, sort of, it is 7 stories high...) somewhere in downtown
Montreal and guess what? It's your job to @{"fix" link play} it!

  That electrical problem messed up the lighting system in the
building and even the engineers at Hydro-Quebec (the provincial
electrical power company) are puzzled as to what has to be done.
That's where you come in the picture: you have to turn off all
lights in that building.

  Sounds simple? But there's a catch: when you turn on or off one
of the lights, some other lights randomly come on or off (depending
on their state), in fact one of the lights may turn on or off as
many as 12 lights.

  When you get all the lights turned off, the game displays the
number of moves you made and you get another building where you
have to fix things, er, turn the lights off...

  Have fun!

